						               													<description>2 Player game.&amp;#10;Each player is a hunter who controls 8 catchers.&amp;#10;The board is a 5x5 field with additional lines of 3 fields at each border. It has jungle fields (light green), impenetrable jungle (dark green) and savannas (yellow). &amp;#10;There are 2 sets of 6 different animals and 1 lion. &amp;#10;Before the game starts, the animals are placed on their fixed fields. The lion in the middle field.&amp;#10;The catchers are placed by the players on the bottom corners of the 3 fields in front of them and the right corners of the most right fields (all these corners are marked in their color).&amp;#10;On players turn, he is allowed to move 1 of his catchers as far as he wants on the lines between the fields (jungle paths). Other catchers only block the single field not the line of movement. He can move horizontal or vertical or both.&amp;#10;There is a possibility to move also diagonal on yellow fields (if no opponent is on the other corners) or light green (if no animal is on the field).&amp;#10;Every time a player can place 1 of his catchers at each of the four corners around 1 animal he catches this animal and takes it in front of him. He is only allowed to catch 1 animal of each kind.&amp;#10;The lion can only be catched when the player has already all 6 other animals. The player who catches the lion wins.&amp;#10;There is a possibility to reduce the number of catchers of the opponent by surrounding them with 4 catchers (independent of the color) and having the possibility to position 1 of the own catchers at the position of this figure.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
